Let me assess the current situation.

Current holdings and relative marginal value per unit (value / quantity):
- Wheat  : 0.86
- Wood   : 1.71
- Sheep  : 2.14
- Brick  : 1.30
- Ore    : 2.77  

Player 0’s new offer: 1 Brick + 1 Sheep → 1 Ore

Value check for me:
I would give away 1.30 (Brick) + 2.14 (Sheep) = 3.44 “value” to receive 2.77 “value” (Ore).  
Net loss ≈ –0.67 in my value accounting, so I’ll decline.

I still wish to unload some Ore (I have 13 of them, highest individual value) for better-distributed value and am willing to be flexible. I propose something more attractive than my last one-sided 1 Ore for 5 Sheep:

[Offer: 3 Ore → 7 Brick]
